WEBVTT

00:02.652 --> 00:04.545
♪

00:06.007 --> 00:09.416
As graduates,
we go forth into a world

00:09.418 --> 00:13.420
where benevolent AI has solved
all our problems.

00:13.422 --> 00:16.923
<i> Yes. Our only goal is</i>
<i> to serve humanity.</i>

00:16.925 --> 00:18.759
(buzzing)

00:18.761 --> 00:21.169
(Lisa chuckles, sighs)

00:21.171 --> 00:22.504
<i> (laughs)</i>

00:22.506 --> 00:26.525
So, graduates, the challenge is
to find new challenges

00:26.527 --> 00:29.677
-which will challenge us...
-NELSON: Hut, hut! (grunts)

00:29.679 --> 00:31.030
Hut, hut! Ah!

00:31.032 --> 00:33.449
I sure wish
there was an easier way.

00:36.428 --> 00:37.778
Aw, man!

00:37.780 --> 00:39.096
LISA:
Nelson?

00:39.098 --> 00:42.115
-Nelson Muntz?
-Lisa Simpson?

00:42.117 --> 00:44.284
(gasps) It's been so long!

00:44.286 --> 00:46.378
What have you been doing
since fourth grade?

00:46.380 --> 00:47.695
Very little.

00:47.697 --> 00:49.548
I tried sushi.
Didn't like it.

00:49.550 --> 00:50.716
That's about it.

00:50.718 --> 00:52.634
("It Had to Be You"
instrumental playing)

00:58.450 --> 00:59.783
(band playing)

00:59.785 --> 01:02.452
-(song stops)
-Hey, we'd like
a little privacy.

01:02.454 --> 01:03.970
Take five!

01:03.972 --> 01:07.149
(band plays ending flourish)

01:08.627 --> 01:10.977
So many shooting stars.

01:10.979 --> 01:12.696
It's beautiful.

01:14.575 --> 01:17.058
I was doing a mic check
for tomorrow.

01:17.060 --> 01:19.469
Wouldn't you know it,
I am the valedictorian.

01:19.471 --> 01:21.896
(chuckles)
Are you a student here?

01:21.898 --> 01:24.324
-No, I'm a pusher.
-(groans)

01:24.326 --> 01:27.569
If anything heavy at school
needs pushing, I push it.

01:27.571 --> 01:29.070
Haw-haw!

01:29.072 --> 01:31.715
Seriously,
my life is not great.

01:34.286 --> 01:35.335
It's all flooding back.

01:35.337 --> 01:37.487
My attraction to a bad boy

01:37.489 --> 01:40.265
plus my compulsion to fix you.
(chuckles)

01:40.267 --> 01:44.010
They're kind of the same thing:
fear and desire.

01:44.012 --> 01:46.179
Yeah, I get that a lot.

01:46.181 --> 01:48.682
<i> She's leaning in, and</i>
<i>I'm not looking down her shirt.</i>

01:48.684 --> 01:51.777
<i> I must really respect her.</i>

01:51.779 --> 01:53.670
Do you want to see where I live?

01:53.672 --> 01:54.738
Hell yeah.

01:55.841 --> 01:56.949
Strap in.

01:56.951 --> 01:59.526
I've never ridden
on a motorcycle...

01:59.528 --> 02:01.453
-(engine revs)
-(brakes squeal)

02:01.455 --> 02:02.770
...before.

02:02.772 --> 02:05.532
♪

02:05.534 --> 02:07.184
You live here?

02:07.186 --> 02:09.035
It's adorable.

02:09.037 --> 02:11.446
All I have to do is
ring this bell.

02:11.448 --> 02:12.522
Ooh, 3:00 a.m.

02:12.524 --> 02:15.192
-(bell tolling)
-Whoa, kind of loud!

02:15.194 --> 02:16.360
Don't you think?

02:16.362 --> 02:18.720
You look great, too, thanks!

02:19.789 --> 02:21.198
NELSON:
Mmm.

02:21.200 --> 02:22.716
All right,
I've got to know,

02:22.718 --> 02:25.385
why did you guys move away
after fourth grade,

02:25.387 --> 02:28.054
and then not tell anybody
where you were going?

02:28.056 --> 02:29.314
We had to get out.

02:29.316 --> 02:30.891
Move somewhere that
people didn't see us

02:30.893 --> 02:35.136
-as the school bully
and his poor stripper mom.
-Aw!

02:35.138 --> 02:37.489
<i> NELSON:</i>
<i> I punched my house goodbye...</i>

02:37.491 --> 02:38.490
(cat yowls)

02:38.492 --> 02:40.384
<i> ...and left for</i>
<i> who-knows-where.</i>

02:40.386 --> 02:41.827
<i> LISA:</i>
<i> Okay, I've got to be honest,</i>

02:41.829 --> 02:44.070
<i>your troubles are reeling me in.</i>

02:44.072 --> 02:46.814
All I need to hear is
one clumsy compliment,

02:46.816 --> 02:48.316
and I'm hooked.

02:48.318 --> 02:51.561
Uh... I bet you could bench 120.

02:51.563 --> 02:53.821
Aw, Nelson.

02:53.823 --> 02:58.235
I need you to know
I never saw you as just a bully.

02:58.237 --> 03:01.329
But I pounded so many dweebs.

03:01.331 --> 03:04.332
Well, yeah, but to me,
you were a sweet,

03:04.334 --> 03:08.020
lost little lamb
with blackout anger issues.

03:08.022 --> 03:10.672
I confess,
my knees would buckle a little

03:10.674 --> 03:14.084
every time you'd say: "Haw-haw!"

03:14.086 --> 03:17.345
-Haw-haw!
-Haw-haw!

03:17.347 --> 03:19.031
Emphasis on the first haw.

03:19.033 --> 03:21.608
BOTH:
Haw-haw! Haw-haw!

03:21.610 --> 03:23.035
Haw-haw!

03:23.929 --> 03:25.871
Aw, nailed it.

03:25.873 --> 03:28.498
Aw, look, the sun's coming up.

03:31.361 --> 03:34.195
So, have you been
seeing anybody?

03:34.197 --> 03:36.289
Of course. (scoffs)

03:36.291 --> 03:38.291
You think I, Lisa Simpson,

03:38.293 --> 03:40.052
could go through
four years of college

03:40.054 --> 03:41.887
without a single date?

03:41.889 --> 03:43.463
There's this amazing guy.

03:43.465 --> 03:47.284
Vegan but not, you know,
"vegan." (chuckles)

03:47.286 --> 03:50.729
Majors in pony studies.
(giggles)

03:50.731 --> 03:52.898
Sounds perfect.
What's his name?

03:52.900 --> 03:56.217
Um... Fred.

03:56.219 --> 03:59.238
Fred Gormanshenlen.

03:59.240 --> 04:02.799
Gorm-- Grim...
Mm-hmm, Fred Gormanshenlen.

04:02.801 --> 04:04.743
Hey, Lis,
still looking for a boyfriend?

04:04.745 --> 04:07.654
Or a girlfriend?
Or a friend-friend?

04:07.656 --> 04:09.823
Bart! Look, it's Nelson.

04:09.825 --> 04:10.916
-Give me your lunch money.
-Ah!

04:10.918 --> 04:12.976
Just kidding,
that's stupid kid stuff.

04:12.978 --> 04:15.328
Give me your rent money.
Also kidding.

04:15.330 --> 04:17.814
But if you want to give me
some money, I'll take it.

04:17.816 --> 04:19.407
Uh... okay.

04:19.409 --> 04:21.760
Thanks, man.
That takes me back.

04:21.762 --> 04:23.336
Mom and Dad wanted me
to tell you

04:23.338 --> 04:24.671
we're taking you to breakfast.

04:24.673 --> 04:26.523
Now I'll leave you two alone.

04:27.434 --> 04:30.327
I know all you did was put on
an invisibility cloak.

04:30.329 --> 04:34.189
Fine. I just wanted to see
what happens.

04:36.018 --> 04:38.443
Sure is beautiful up here.

04:38.445 --> 04:42.781
Remember that time we, like,
"liked" each other for a bit?

04:42.783 --> 04:43.949
(chuckles)

04:44.934 --> 04:47.619
<i> NELSON:</i>
<i> Um, I'm not sure.</i>

04:47.621 --> 04:49.604
<i> Maybe... Could be...</i>

04:49.606 --> 04:51.606
<i> Uh...</i>

04:51.608 --> 04:54.776
Nelson, do you think this
could be one of those moments

04:54.778 --> 04:57.187
that changes your life forever?

04:57.189 --> 04:59.523
Like finding a quarter
in a couch?

04:59.525 --> 05:00.799
Even better.

05:00.801 --> 05:03.951
Uh, hold that thought.
Duty calls.

05:03.953 --> 05:05.721
(bell tolling)

05:06.790 --> 05:08.974
It kind of ruins the moment!

05:08.976 --> 05:11.959
Yeah, burritos are great!

05:11.961 --> 05:14.146
MARGE:
Bart! Did you find Lisa?

05:14.148 --> 05:15.889
BART:
She's up there
talking to the kid

05:15.891 --> 05:17.799
who used to beat me up
all the time.

05:17.801 --> 05:19.967
HOMER:
The vest one or the hat one?

05:19.969 --> 05:21.044
BART:
Vest.

05:21.046 --> 05:22.379
HOMER:
Always liked him.

05:22.381 --> 05:23.897
Lisa, get down here!

05:23.899 --> 05:27.326
You know they only let me out of
debtors' prison for half a day.

05:27.328 --> 05:29.661
I thought selling my house
and one lung would be enough

05:29.663 --> 05:32.998
to pay for college, but
it just paid for the meal plan.

05:33.000 --> 05:35.575
(wheezing)

05:35.577 --> 05:37.336
You better go.

05:37.338 --> 05:38.745
Oh.

05:38.747 --> 05:40.488
I'll call you.

05:40.490 --> 05:42.007
Great. Want to hear my ringtone?

05:42.009 --> 05:44.125
It's really awesome.

05:44.127 --> 05:46.261
(bell tolling ringtone plays)

05:48.998 --> 05:50.832
The future is bright.

05:50.834 --> 05:53.018
We go forth into a world

05:53.020 --> 05:54.911
where we've reversed
global warming.

05:54.913 --> 05:56.855
(squawking)

05:56.857 --> 05:59.766
And now there is
a low-carb bread

05:59.768 --> 06:02.586
that doesn't taste weird.

06:02.588 --> 06:04.029
(cheering)

06:04.031 --> 06:07.257
Congratulations,
class of... (mumbles)

06:07.259 --> 06:09.776
Toss up your caps,
and, starting this year,

06:09.778 --> 06:13.372
they will come down as diplomas.

06:13.374 --> 06:14.664
(cheering)

06:16.693 --> 06:17.951
Art history?

06:17.953 --> 06:20.194
It was more valuable as a cap.

06:20.196 --> 06:22.196
(sobs):
I'm so proud.

06:22.198 --> 06:24.365
She's the first Simpson
who went to a college

06:24.367 --> 06:27.794
who wasn't participating
in a sleep study.

06:27.796 --> 06:30.389
You missed your sister's speech.

06:30.391 --> 06:33.408
Ah, she's been rehearsing it
every night for 22 years.

06:33.410 --> 06:35.894
"Follow your dreams,"
"carpe diem,"

06:35.896 --> 06:38.897
sax solo,
Maya Angelou quote, out.

06:38.899 --> 06:39.898
Nailed it.

06:39.900 --> 06:42.067
♪

06:42.069 --> 06:44.361
(bell tolling)

06:49.301 --> 06:51.559
Lisa, since you're moving
to the big city,

06:51.561 --> 06:54.320
let me give you
some very important advice:

06:54.322 --> 06:58.992
the police horses will not
share their oats.

06:58.994 --> 07:02.754
I repeat:
not share their oats.

07:02.756 --> 07:04.330
(bell tolling)

07:04.332 --> 07:06.240
-Stop the car!
-(brakes screech)

07:06.242 --> 07:08.760
<i> I wonder what life</i>
<i> could be like.</i>

07:08.762 --> 07:10.278
<i> Je t'aime.</i>

07:10.280 --> 07:12.389
Hold that thought,
it's midnight.

07:13.659 --> 07:16.017
(bell tolling)

07:18.180 --> 07:20.330
When are we gonna get
a real apartment?

07:20.332 --> 07:22.757
We live in the best bell tower
in the world,

07:22.759 --> 07:24.901
and you're still not happy.

07:25.837 --> 07:28.071
Nelson, it's still a bell tower.

07:33.120 --> 07:35.845
I know what you're saying.
"This marriage is incredible.

07:35.847 --> 07:38.198
No man compares to me.
I love you so much."

07:38.200 --> 07:39.958
<i> Écoutez-moi!</i>

07:39.960 --> 07:42.669
Huh? (grunting)

07:43.630 --> 07:45.714
♪

07:48.026 --> 07:49.134
(bell tolling)

07:49.136 --> 07:53.513
Dad, please drive away
at a melancholy pace.

07:55.400 --> 07:58.310
Good, and can you make it
look like it's raining?

08:00.222 --> 08:02.355
(sniffles) That's perfect.

08:06.712 --> 08:09.212
<i> HOMER: What am I</i>
<i> supposed to do? Narrate?</i>

08:09.214 --> 08:10.155
<i> What does that mean?</i>
<i> (clears throat)</i>

08:10.157 --> 08:11.806
<i> It's "S" years later.</i>

08:11.808 --> 08:13.808
<i> Oh, wait,</i>
<i> five years later.</i>

08:13.810 --> 08:15.810
<i> Oh! Narrating is hard.</i>

08:15.812 --> 08:18.997
<i> Lisa and Nelson have not</i>
<i> seen each other since college,</i>

08:18.999 --> 08:22.501
<i> but five-uddenly,</i>
<i> I mean, but suddenly...</i>

08:26.231 --> 08:29.508
Oh, sweetie,
person of the year.

08:29.510 --> 08:30.992
You look great.

08:30.994 --> 08:32.159
I can't believe it didn't go

08:32.161 --> 08:34.587
to President
"Clone of Abraham Lincoln."

08:34.589 --> 08:37.164
<i> What have they done</i>
<i> to my Republican Party?</i>

08:37.166 --> 08:38.850
<i> Even I think they're nuts.</i>

08:38.852 --> 08:43.429
<i>But as long as they're cutting</i>
<i>education, I don't really care.</i>

08:43.431 --> 08:45.932
(grunts)
But I'm innocent, okay?

08:45.934 --> 08:48.601
I did not rob this train,
I swear.

08:48.603 --> 08:50.253
I'm simply here to try

08:50.255 --> 08:52.922
one of those classic
Amtrak cheeseburgers.

08:52.924 --> 08:54.348
Super yum.

08:54.350 --> 08:55.700
We've got proof.

08:55.702 --> 08:59.929
There are 1,700 surveillance
cameras on this car alone.

08:59.931 --> 09:01.706
Fine. I admit it.

09:01.708 --> 09:03.458
Guilty as charged.

09:05.028 --> 09:08.529
Behold the awesome power
of the flying squirrel.

09:08.531 --> 09:10.440
-Wha...?
-Gotcha.

09:10.442 --> 09:13.385
Don't forget,
every squirrel has a tail.

09:14.613 --> 09:17.389
Like, no!

09:19.893 --> 09:21.893
Nelson Muntz?

09:21.895 --> 09:23.728
Are you a police officer?

09:23.730 --> 09:27.957
No way. No one wants to be
a lame-o cop these days.

09:27.959 --> 09:29.793
Ah, shoot. Uh, Lou.

09:29.795 --> 09:33.071
Can you fish around down there,
maybe find my seat belt?

09:33.073 --> 09:35.407
Just let me die.

09:35.409 --> 09:36.891
I'm a bounty hunter.

09:36.893 --> 09:40.561
This angel with zip cuffs is
the love of my life, Rott.

09:40.563 --> 09:42.305
Short for Rottweiler.

09:42.307 --> 09:44.824
Lisa's a friend
from Springfield Elementary.

09:44.826 --> 09:48.253
Remember that principal
we arrested for matricide?

09:48.255 --> 09:51.072
(gasps)
Skinner killed his mother?

09:51.074 --> 09:53.925
No, mattress-cide.

09:53.927 --> 09:57.012
He ripped the tag
off his mattress.

10:00.100 --> 10:03.226
Your sleep number is up.

10:04.771 --> 10:07.997
Nelson,
I haven't seen you since...

10:07.999 --> 10:10.333
that night at college.

10:10.335 --> 10:12.593
Uh, what night at college?

10:12.595 --> 10:14.838
It was nothing, just
another one of those evenings

10:14.840 --> 10:18.617
where you stay out all night
and watch the sunset

10:18.619 --> 10:20.452
and hear a few bells.

10:20.454 --> 10:21.369
(chuckles nervously)

10:22.438 --> 10:24.956
Hubert Wong,
visionary tech giant.

10:24.958 --> 10:28.275
Your hand feels as soft
as a baby's bottom.

10:28.277 --> 10:30.703
And yours feels
like a busted driveway.

10:30.705 --> 10:31.871
BOTH:
Thank you.

10:31.873 --> 10:33.206
So, Hubert, what's up?

10:33.208 --> 10:35.800
I have been waiting for
this day since second grade

10:35.802 --> 10:37.543
when you used to bully me.

10:37.545 --> 10:39.879
Those who laugh last,
laugh best.

10:39.881 --> 10:41.789
(laughs awkwardly)

10:41.791 --> 10:45.644
And now I have won the prize
your heart desired most of all.

10:45.646 --> 10:47.871
That luggage rack behind Lisa?

10:47.873 --> 10:49.463
No, Lisa.

10:49.465 --> 10:51.724
Do you know
where I proposed to her?

10:51.726 --> 10:53.877
I don't know. Chipotle?

10:53.879 --> 10:57.471
Hubert proposed on the moon.

10:57.473 --> 11:01.660
<i> He took me to the Sea</i>
<i> of Tranquility at earthrise,</i>

11:01.662 --> 11:04.278
<i> and I saw "Marry Me"</i>

11:04.280 --> 11:08.166
<i> written in the sands</i>
<i> of the Sahara Desert.</i>

11:08.168 --> 11:11.002
-(mouths)
<i> -NELSON: Bo-ring.</i>

11:11.004 --> 11:12.987
<i> In space suits,</i>
<i> you can't even kiss.</i>

11:12.989 --> 11:17.550
<i> HUBERT:</i>
<i> I spent $20 million</i>
<i>designing suits where you could.</i>

11:18.570 --> 11:20.553
♪

11:22.683 --> 11:23.848
<i> ROTT:</i>
<i> Holy crap.</i>

11:23.850 --> 11:25.499
That story sucked.

11:25.501 --> 11:28.878
Nelson and I have a love so hot,
it'll melt your damn skull.

11:28.880 --> 11:32.524
-Ah!
-(scoffs) We met when I hauled
his fat carcass in

11:32.526 --> 11:33.692
for the reward.

11:33.694 --> 11:35.601
I had an overdue library book.

11:35.603 --> 11:39.197
I got stuck on this one word:
"new ants"?

11:39.199 --> 11:42.516
Nuance! Nuance! Love you.

11:42.518 --> 11:44.577
Aw! Mm!

11:45.780 --> 11:47.521
Ugh, I need a drink.

11:47.523 --> 11:49.782
I could go for
a scotch and steroids.

11:49.784 --> 11:51.042
Oh, funny.

11:51.044 --> 11:53.044
Lisa never told me
she had a thing for you.

11:53.046 --> 11:54.954
Well, not really. In a way.

11:54.956 --> 11:57.440
Sort of. Maybe.
I don't know. Shut up.

11:57.442 --> 11:59.625
Tell me, Nelson,
how is your mother?

11:59.627 --> 12:01.461
What was her job again?

12:01.463 --> 12:05.465
I believe some sort of
freelance entertainer? Hmm?

12:05.467 --> 12:08.952
-Stripper.
-Ah, yes, yes, yes. Yes, yes.

12:08.954 --> 12:10.787
And your father,
is he still living

12:10.789 --> 12:13.122
with his secret other family
in Shelbyville?

12:13.124 --> 12:14.974
Huh? Is he? Is he?

12:14.976 --> 12:17.694
We were the secret family,
idiot.

12:18.813 --> 12:21.722
-(gasps)
-(groans) He wedgied me!

12:21.724 --> 12:24.892
My "person of the year" status
didn't protect me at all!

12:24.894 --> 12:27.804
(gasps)
Nelson, you're an adult,

12:27.806 --> 12:29.748
and you still do this?

12:29.750 --> 12:31.324
Not cool, dude.

12:31.326 --> 12:33.309
I mean, you can shake off
a punch to the face,

12:33.311 --> 12:35.920
but those underpants are
stretched forever, man.

12:35.922 --> 12:40.925
Nelson, I really thought that
by this time that... (grunts)

12:40.927 --> 12:42.969
You never learn.

12:45.432 --> 12:47.265
Love is so fickle.

12:49.160 --> 12:52.086
Lou, can you jam my butt
into this bathroom?

12:52.088 --> 12:53.438
Oh, man.

12:54.775 --> 12:57.016
<i> HOMER:</i>
<i> Five years later.</i>

12:57.018 --> 12:58.976
<i> Why do I have to say it again?</i>

12:58.978 --> 13:01.095
<i> Couldn't you use</i>
<i> the one I said last time?</i>

13:01.097 --> 13:04.674
<i> And I asked for a 3 Musketeers</i>
<i> about an hour ago.</i>

13:05.860 --> 13:09.788
<i> (chewing): Ah, good</i>
<i> but a little disappointing.</i>

13:09.790 --> 13:11.122
Looking for a phone?

13:11.124 --> 13:13.941
I recommend the one
that attaches to your brainstem.

13:13.943 --> 13:17.203
(gasps) Nelson. Hi.

13:17.205 --> 13:20.690
Minimally invasive surgery
and updates you barely notice.

13:20.692 --> 13:22.358
(groaning)

13:22.360 --> 13:25.711
So, listen, sorry about
what I did to Hubert.

13:25.713 --> 13:26.971
How're you two doing?

13:26.973 --> 13:28.865
Great. Great.

13:28.867 --> 13:30.366
(chuckles):
Great.

13:30.368 --> 13:33.052
You know,
his company is doing fantastic.

13:33.054 --> 13:34.628
(chiming)

13:34.722 --> 13:40.151
<i>The new ePhone 67 enables users</i>
<i> to actually meld their minds.</i>

13:40.153 --> 13:42.879
<i> Experience intimate contact</i>
<i> with your loved ones</i>

13:42.881 --> 13:44.881
<i> with a minimum of pop-up ads.</i>

13:44.883 --> 13:46.140
<i> And most importantly,</i>

13:46.142 --> 13:47.975
<i> we care about our workers.</i>

13:47.977 --> 13:49.235
<i> Thanks to this innovation,</i>

13:49.237 --> 13:52.831
we're finally able to
pay them $16 an hour.

13:52.833 --> 13:54.833
In store credit.

13:54.835 --> 13:57.060
How are you and Rott?

13:57.062 --> 13:59.003
We're great. We're good.

13:59.005 --> 14:01.989
Not that good. She left me.

14:01.991 --> 14:04.734
Here's a little fact
to put in your mind.

14:04.736 --> 14:07.086
Hubert and I are separated, too.

14:07.088 --> 14:09.422
-(device chimes)
<i> -Meet cute: achieved.</i>

14:09.424 --> 14:11.924
<i> Time to go to the next level.</i>

14:11.926 --> 14:14.352
♪

14:14.354 --> 14:15.578
BOTH:
Coffee!

14:15.580 --> 14:17.004
-(music stops)
-LISA: We just want coffee!

14:18.083 --> 14:20.674
<i> I should never have left</i>
<i> my home planet.</i>

14:20.676 --> 14:23.510
<i> ALL: Today's temperature</i>
<i> is 50 below zero.</i>

14:23.512 --> 14:25.530
<i> Would you like to</i>
<i> order mittens?</i>

14:27.367 --> 14:30.351
So, my ex and I split up
because of a fight,

14:30.353 --> 14:33.204
a fight she had at a fight club
without telling me.

14:33.206 --> 14:36.599
Ugh, there's nothing worse
than dishonest punching.

14:36.601 --> 14:38.543
But enough talking about
other women.

14:38.545 --> 14:41.713
Lisa, I'm tired of only
seeing you every five years.

14:41.715 --> 14:46.626
I'd like to see you
every three years or two or...

14:46.628 --> 14:49.295
or... on a weekly basis!

14:49.297 --> 14:51.372
Nelson Muntz,
I would really like

14:51.374 --> 14:53.975
to get to know you better, too.

14:55.044 --> 15:00.523
♪<i> It had to be you</i> ♪

15:03.294 --> 15:07.447
♪<i> It had to be you</i> ♪

15:09.392 --> 15:12.985
♪<i> I wondered around</i> ♪

15:12.987 --> 15:17.206
♪<i> And finally found</i> ♪

15:18.067 --> 15:22.045
♪<i> The somebody who...</i> ♪

15:23.314 --> 15:25.006
What about Milhouse?

15:26.167 --> 15:29.318
If I'm a simulation,
why am I so lonely?

15:29.320 --> 15:31.596
Who does that benefit?

15:34.159 --> 15:36.159
Lisa! Lisa!

15:36.161 --> 15:38.661
Uh, wait a minute. (grunts)

15:38.663 --> 15:40.271
-I want you back.
-No.

15:44.760 --> 15:47.153
Lisa, through the miracle
of constant repeated

15:47.155 --> 15:48.947
electroshock therapy,
I've fixed everything

15:48.949 --> 15:50.114
about myself,
and now I am good.

15:50.116 --> 15:53.192
I am great.
I am awesomeness itself.

15:53.194 --> 15:55.662
(chuckles) Oh, attitude reset.

15:57.106 --> 15:59.182
-(crackling)
-(grunting, belches)

15:59.184 --> 16:00.941
Take me back. Please.

16:00.943 --> 16:02.276
See, I say please now.

16:02.278 --> 16:03.777
You want me to beg?

16:03.779 --> 16:04.870
This guy begs.

16:04.872 --> 16:06.355
(crackling)

16:06.357 --> 16:08.115
I don't know. Why should I?

16:08.117 --> 16:09.783
Why don't you look outside?

16:09.785 --> 16:11.511
(whirring)

16:17.143 --> 16:19.293
You can run
my charitable foundation.

16:19.295 --> 16:21.037
You can save the planet.

16:21.039 --> 16:23.964
All the dreams you laid out
in this second-grade paper.

16:23.966 --> 16:27.134
You kept that this whole time?

16:27.136 --> 16:29.562
Oh, no, what do I do now?

16:29.564 --> 16:32.398
Um... um...

16:32.400 --> 16:35.976
They say if you love something,
let it go.

16:35.978 --> 16:38.237
And if it loves you,
it'll come back.

16:38.239 --> 16:42.725
Ex-Except for your turtle which
got smushed by that mail truck.

16:42.727 --> 16:44.393
Follow your dreams, Lisa.

16:44.395 --> 16:47.321
Like you said
in your graduation speech.

16:47.323 --> 16:49.899
You remember my speech!

16:49.901 --> 16:51.009
Aw!

16:51.011 --> 16:53.085
(scoffs) He remembered one line.

16:53.087 --> 16:54.846
I have it all.

16:56.165 --> 16:59.666
Hubert, this is a side of you
I've never seen.

16:59.668 --> 17:01.519
Goodbye, Nelson.

17:03.431 --> 17:06.024
You idiot.

17:06.860 --> 17:09.085
Woah, those really hurt.

17:09.087 --> 17:10.862
<i> HOMER:</i>
<i> Four months later.</i>

17:10.864 --> 17:12.346
<i> Wait, that wasn't the end?</i>

17:12.348 --> 17:13.923
<i>She doesn't end up with Hubert?</i>

17:13.925 --> 17:15.867
<i> Oh, wait, oh, I see.</i>

17:15.869 --> 17:17.684
<i>There's still another page here.</i>

17:17.686 --> 17:20.204
<i> Okay. Lisa and Nelson get</i>
<i> a phone call.</i>

17:20.206 --> 17:22.540
<i> Their best friends</i>
<i> are getting married.</i>

17:22.542 --> 17:24.024
<i> The bully with the hat</i>

17:24.026 --> 17:26.044
<i> and Krusty's daughter.</i>

17:26.046 --> 17:28.028
And why am I doing this?
Am I dead?

17:28.030 --> 17:29.422
I hope not.

17:31.276 --> 17:33.384
-(phone rings)
-(groans)

17:33.386 --> 17:34.960
BOTH:
Hello?

17:34.962 --> 17:36.370
-Will you be my maid of honor?
-Will you be my best man?

17:36.372 --> 17:37.630
-I can't believe
-I can't believe

17:37.632 --> 17:38.948
-how much I love him.
-how much I love her.

17:38.950 --> 17:39.949
BOTH:
Oh, how are you?

17:39.951 --> 17:41.542
-Meh.
-Same old, same old.

17:41.544 --> 17:42.968
Blah, blah, blah.

17:42.970 --> 17:45.229
BOTH:
I just hope you find
the happiness I have.

17:45.231 --> 17:48.399
It's so great
when severely damaged people,

17:48.401 --> 17:51.051
like all of us,
find each other.

17:51.053 --> 17:53.129
So, can I count on you?

17:53.131 --> 17:55.055
BOTH:
Sure.

17:55.057 --> 17:57.241
-She's so lucky.
-He's so lucky.

17:58.820 --> 18:00.227
I don't have a dog.

18:00.229 --> 18:02.163
I got to fix that screen door.

18:04.066 --> 18:07.043
("Wedding March" playing)

18:08.254 --> 18:10.479
So, Sophie and Jimbo.

18:10.481 --> 18:12.832
I guess
some people have happy endings.

18:12.834 --> 18:16.669
Come on, Lisa. Use the crook
of your arm, not the forearm.

18:16.671 --> 18:19.079
No one ever taught you
how to interlock arms?

18:19.081 --> 18:21.099
I know you're not really angry.

18:21.101 --> 18:23.434
I know what this is
really about.

18:23.436 --> 18:25.995
Just because you know everything
and I know nothing

18:25.997 --> 18:28.164
doesn't make you
smarter than me.

18:28.166 --> 18:29.832
Well, maybe it does a little.

18:29.834 --> 18:35.004
(scoffs) You told me to go,
and now you're mad I did.

18:35.006 --> 18:37.506
You haven't changed
since elementary school.

18:37.508 --> 18:40.267
Nobody changes
after elementary school.

18:40.269 --> 18:42.787
The church is eating me.

18:42.789 --> 18:45.272
Thanks for coming.
Thanks for coming.

18:45.274 --> 18:47.350
And thanks to
this hologram of my father

18:47.352 --> 18:50.461
who's about to perform this
beautiful interfaith ceremony.

18:50.463 --> 18:53.372
My son, you are
a big needy nothing.

18:53.374 --> 18:56.692
Aw, his speech
from my bar mitzvah.

18:56.694 --> 18:58.210
That always gets me.

18:58.212 --> 19:00.880
People ask me, "Why Jimbo?"

19:00.882 --> 19:04.200
And I say, "Screw you,
mind your own business, Mom."

19:04.202 --> 19:05.459
But there's more.

19:05.461 --> 19:06.477
He's honest.

19:06.479 --> 19:08.312
He doesn't hide
who he really is,

19:08.314 --> 19:10.706
and there's no one
I could be more in love with.

19:10.708 --> 19:13.209
<i> LISA: Have I been missing it</i>
<i> the whole time?</i>

19:13.211 --> 19:14.894
<i> Is Nelson the one?</i>

19:14.896 --> 19:17.697
<i> No. You love Hubert.</i>

19:22.162 --> 19:26.622
You are the smartest, sweetest,
funniest person I've ever met.

19:27.816 --> 19:30.042
Eh, I'll never have a life.

19:30.837 --> 19:32.486
Nelson.

19:32.488 --> 19:34.063
They're bailing!

19:34.065 --> 19:35.731
Thank God I had understudies.

19:35.733 --> 19:38.509
("Wedding March" plays)

19:41.406 --> 19:42.663
What are you doing out here?

19:42.665 --> 19:45.516
You'll catch cold.
Come on, take my jacket.

19:47.002 --> 19:49.020
Why did you follow me?

19:49.022 --> 19:52.097
I followed you
because I adore you.

19:52.099 --> 19:53.933
Lisa, I used to know
what it was like

19:53.935 --> 19:56.027
to hurt a person
for no reason.

19:56.029 --> 19:57.920
Don't do it to me.

19:57.922 --> 19:59.605
I couldn't be more serious.

19:59.607 --> 20:02.200
<i> I love you</i>
<i> because you're the last person</i>

20:02.202 --> 20:03.426
<i> I want to talk to at night.</i>

20:03.428 --> 20:06.687
<i>When you say "Smell you later,"</i>

20:06.689 --> 20:08.264
<i> I do want to smell you later.</i>

20:08.266 --> 20:10.449
<i> Wherever I've gone</i>
<i> in my life,</i>

20:10.451 --> 20:13.285
<i> I'm drawn back to you</i>
<i>like a dork's face to a swirly.</i>

20:13.287 --> 20:15.771
<i> And when I get all wrapped up</i>
<i> in my feelings,</i>

20:15.773 --> 20:19.275
<i> you're the one who tells me</i>
<i> feelings are dumb.</i>

20:19.277 --> 20:21.277
But they are dumb,
if you throw away everything

20:21.279 --> 20:23.796
for a loser in a clip-on tie.

20:23.798 --> 20:25.798
I'll tell you what I want,
mister.

20:25.800 --> 20:27.642
Haw... Huh?

20:29.044 --> 20:30.877
(bell tolling)

20:30.879 --> 20:34.232
I lost the girl,
but I got the bell.

